title: Eight more Covid-19 deaths, 295 new cases diagnosed
description: Eight more people have died from Covid-19 in Ireland and 295 new cases have been diagnosed today.
content:
Eight more people have died from Covid-19 in Ireland and 295 new cases have been diagnosed today.
There have now been 54 Covid-19 related deaths in Ireland.
There are now 2,910 confirmed cases of Covid-19 in the Republic.
